## 5. KTU 2024 Scheme Examination Question Bank & Topic Recap

### 5.1 Part A Questions (3 Marks Each)

**Q1. [KTU University Exam - Dec 2023]**
*Define a Sub Class. How is it different from a Super Class?*

**Model Answer:**
A **Sub Class** is a class that inherits the properties and methods of another class (called the Super Class). It uses the `extends` keyword in Java or `:` colon syntax in C++. The key differences are:

| Aspect | Super Class | Sub Class |
|---|---|---|
| Role | Provides inherited members | Receives inherited members |
| Position | Higher in hierarchy | Lower in hierarchy |
| Keyword | `parent`, `base` | `child`, `derived` |

*(3 marks — definition 1, difference table 2)*

---

**Q2. [KTU University Exam - June 2024]**
*Explain the term "is-a" relationship with respect to Sub Classes.*

**Model Answer:**
The **"is-a" relationship** is the semantic relationship between a Sub Class and its Super Class. If class `Dog` extends `Animal`, then `Dog is-a Animal` — meaning every Dog object possesses all the essential qualities of an Animal. This is in contrast to the **"has-a" relationship** (composition), where a class *contains* another class as a member.

Example: A `Car` is-a `Vehicle`, but a `Car` has-a `Engine`.

*(3 marks — concept 2, example 1)*

