**(b)** Java Program:

```java
class BankAccount {                        // SUPER CLASS
    protected double balance;

    BankAccount(double initialBalance) {
        this.balance = initialBalance;
    }

    public void deposit(double amount) {
        balance += amount;
    }

    public void withdraw(double amount) {
        if (amount <= balance) {
            balance -= amount;
        } else {
            System.out.println("Insufficient balance.");
        }
    }
}

class SavingsAccount extends BankAccount { // SUB CLASS
    private double interestRate;

    SavingsAccount(double initialBalance, double rate) {
        super(initialBalance);
        this.interestRate = rate;
    }

    public void computeInterest(int years) {
        double interest = balance * interestRate * years;
        System.out.println("Interest for " + years + " years: " + interest);
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SavingsAccount sa = new SavingsAccount(10000, 0.05);
        sa.deposit(5000);
        sa.withdraw(2000);
        sa.computeInterest(3);
    }
}
```

**Sample Output Trace:**

$$\text{Balance after deposit} = 10000 + 5000 = 15000$$

$$\text{Balance after withdrawal} = 15000 - 2000 = 13000$$

$$\text{Interest} = 13000 \times 0.05 \times 3 = 1950$$

