#### **Question B (14 Marks)** — Alternative Choice [KTU University Exam - June 2023]

**(a)** Discuss the access specifiers `private`, `protected`, and `public` in the context of Sub Class inheritance. Give a C++ example to illustrate. *(7 marks)*

**(b)** What is method overriding? Demonstrate with a C++ program where a Sub Class overrides a function from the Super Class. *(7 marks)*

**Model Solution:**

**(a)** Detailed access specifier explanation (refer to Section 2.3 table). C++ example:

```cpp
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

class Base {
private:
    int a = 10;                  // NOT accessible in Sub Class
protected:
    int b = 20;                  // Accessible in Sub Class
public:
    int c = 30;                  // Accessible everywhere
};

class Derived : public Base {
public:
    void show() {
        // cout << a;            // ERROR: a is private
        cout << "b = " << b << endl;   // OK: protected
        cout << "c = " << c << endl;   // OK: public
    }
