### 5.3 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

- ✅ A **Sub Class** inherits from a Super Class using `extends` (Java) or `:` (C++).
- ✅ Sub Class objects contain a **base-class sub-object** plus their own members.
- ✅ Constructor order: **Base → Derived**. Destructor order: **Derived → Base**.
- ✅ `private` members of the Super Class are **never** directly accessible in the Sub Class.
- ✅ `protected` members are accessible in Sub Classes but remain hidden from unrelated classes.
- ✅ Method overriding enables **runtime polymorphism** — requires `virtual` in C++ (implicit in Java).
- ✅ Java supports only **single inheritance** for classes; multiple inheritance is achieved via **interfaces**.
- ✅ The "is-a" relationship denotes inheritance; "has-a" denotes composition.
- ✅ Upcasting is automatic; downcasting requires explicit casting and type checking.
- ✅ A Sub Class can be further extended — creating **multilevel inheritance** chains.
- ✅ The **Diamond Problem** is resolved in Java using interfaces and in C++ using **virtual inheritance**.

