## ⚠️ KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Common Pitfalls

> [!WARNING]
> **Where KTU students lose marks on Interface questions:**
> 1. **Writing `public abstract` explicitly inside an interface** — *not wrong, but examiners deduct for redundancy if the question demands "default behaviour of an interface".*
> 2. **Forgetting to write `public` in the implementing class's method override** — interface methods are `public` by default, so the override **must** also be `public`. Writing `void pay()` (package-private) causes a *compilation error* and zero marks.
> 3. **Confusing `extends` and `implements`** — class uses `extends` for class, `implements` for interface; interface uses `extends` for interface.
> 4. **Saying "interface can have constructors"** — this is a guaranteed mark-cutter. Interfaces **cannot** have constructors because they cannot be instantiated.
> 5. **Forgetting that interface variables are `final`** — you cannot reassign them. The code `PaymentGateway.TRANSACTION_FEE = 5.0;` will not compile.
> 6. **Mixing up default methods with abstract methods in inheritance** — a class that inherits a default method may *choose* to override or inherit; but an abstract method *must* be overridden (or the class must also be abstract).

