### Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

> [!TIP]
> **High-Yield Rapid Revision Checklist — Event Handling in Swings:**

- The **Delegation Event Model** has three participants: **Source**, **Event**, **Listener**.
- Registration is **mandatory**: `source.addXxxListener(listenerObj);`.
- All event classes extend `java.util.EventObject`; AWT event classes extend `java.awt.AWTEvent`.
- `ActionListener` has **1 method** (`actionPerformed`); `MouseListener` has **5**; `WindowListener` has **7**.
- **Adapter classes** provide empty default implementations — override only what you need.
- Common adapters: `MouseAdapter`, `KeyAdapter`, `WindowAdapter`, `FocusAdapter`.
- `KeyEvent.getKeyChar()` returns the character; `KeyEvent.getKeyCode()` returns the virtual key code.
- `MouseEvent.getPoint()` returns a `Point` (x, y); `getX()` and `getY()` return coordinates separately.
- `WindowEvent` fires on the **JFrame** itself, registered via `this.addWindowListener(...)`.
- **Anonymous inner classes** are the most idiomatic Swing listener implementation.
- `setDefaultCloseOperation(EXIT_ON_CLOSE)` and `WindowListener.windowClosing` are **independent** mechanisms.
- `JOptionPane.showConfirmDialog` returns `YES_OPTION`, `NO_OPTION`, or `CANCEL_OPTION` — must compare with these constants.
- **Inner class access to outer class**: use `OuterClassName.this` to disambiguate.
- Component updates must happen on the **Event Dispatch Thread (EDT)** for thread safety in production code; for KTU exams, direct updates inside handlers are acceptable.
- **Compile vs Runtime errors to watch**: missing override → compile error; missing `addXxxListener` → silent runtime failure.

